Run ./update_configs to copy dotfiles. Log out and in to get PATH updates.

# Aptitude packages. `sudo apt install $PKG_NAME`.

redshift-gtk  # (And set it to autostart!)
git
tmux
i3
xfce4
xfce4-goodies
xclip  # For system-clipboard integration with tmux and nvim.
ranger
highlight  # For syntax highlighting in ranger.
tldr
expect  # For `unbuffer`.
rlwrap
gcc  # Rust needs a linker.
python3-pip

# Install Rust, plus a few commandline utils via `cargo install $PKG`:

ripgrep
fd-find
bat
hexyl
cargo-watch

# For Rust development. (Racer needs nightly Rust.)
rustup component add rust-src
rustup toolchain add nightly
cargo +nightly install racer

# Misc.

To combine i3 with xfce, see steps V, VI, VII, VIII, X of this guide:
https://feeblenerd.blogspot.com/2015/11/pretty-i3-with-xfce.html

# Install the latest stable release of Neovim.
wget https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/stable/nvim.appimage
mkdir -p ~/bin
mv nvim.appimage ~/bin/nvim
chmod +x ~/bin/nvim

# To get deoplete to work:
pip3 install pynvim

# Install fzf.
git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/junegunn/fzf.git ~/.fzf
~/.fzf/install

# Install diff-so-fancy.
git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/so-fancy/diff-so-fancy.git ~/.d-s-f
ln -s ~/.d-s-f/diff-so-fancy ~/bin/diff-so-fancy

For passwordless sudo, append this to /etc/sudoers:
ALL ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

To get capslock to be control in virtual consoles, add this line:
(dumpkeys | head -1; echo keycode 58 = Control) | loadkeys -
to /etc/rc.local and make it executable with the header #!/bin/bash

On Windows, set system env var HOME to "C:\Users\$USERNAME" so Emacs can find
your configs.

# xfce4-terminal settings.

Scrollbar is: Disabled
DejaVu Sans Mono Book 22 point font, or on 1920x1080 screens:
    14pt (=173x46 chars), 19 (127x35), 22 (106x30), 27 (87x25)
Don't display menubar in new windows
Solarized color scheme (light or dark)
Don't show bold text in bright colors
Disable all shortcuts
Autohide mouse pointer
Automatically copy selection to clipboard
